Citation.sTitle: Measurement and Correlation of Solubility of Cefuroxime Acid in Pure and Binary Solvents at Various Temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of cefuroxime acid in four pure solvents and three binary solvents formed by water + acetone, ethanol + acetone, and 2-propanol + acetone at atmospheric pressure has been measured via a laser monitoring observation technique over the temperature range from (278.5 to 313.4) K. The solubility of cefuroxime acid increased with increasing temperature in water, 2-propanol, and ethanol but decreased in acetone. The heat flux measurements by a Differential Scanning Calorimeter (DSC) and solubility with temperature behavior were consistent. The solubility data of cefuroxime acid in pure solvents were correlated by the modified Apelblat equation, and the maximum average absolute error (AAE) was 0.07. The solubility data of cefuroxime acid in binary solvents at various temperatures were fitted by the Jouyban-Acree model, and the maximum AAE was 0.06. The solubility of cefuroxime acid in binary solvents was significantly higher than that in pure solvents and showed a maximum at a specific volume fraction of acetone.
